(4683, 390, 'preparaciones_0_preparacion', 'In a mixing bowl, add 4 cups of all purpose flour, 1 tablespoon of dry yeast, 2 tablespoons of brown sugar and a full tablespoon of salt plus a 1 ½ cups of warm water.'),
(4684, 390, '_preparaciones_0_preparacion', 'field_58606bb7acb51'),
(4685, 390, 'preparaciones_1_preparacion', 'Stir gently until is well-mixed, cover with a cloth and let it rest for 20 minutes.'),
(4686, 390, '_preparaciones_1_preparacion', 'field_58606bb7acb51'),
(4687, 390, 'preparaciones_2_preparacion', 'Now form a line with ½ inch diameter. Cross the ends of the line and twist them, linking them in the end, it´ll look like a ribbon. If you want to, you can also make sticks, circles, rolls or any additional shape using the dough formed.'),
(4688, 390, '_preparaciones_2_preparacion', 'field_58606bb7acb51'),
(4689, 390, 'preparaciones_3_preparacion', 'Place the pieces in the oven covered with aluminum foil. Now mix 1 cup of water and 2 tablespoons of baking soda. Then brush the mixture on top of the pretzels and place them in the pre-heated oven at 356ºF for 15 minutes or until they’re golden brown.'),
(4690, 390, '_preparaciones_3_preparacion', 'field_58606bb7acb51'),
(4691, 390, 'preparaciones_4_preparacion', 'Finally melt 2 Oz. of butter and brush on the cooked pretzels. Then, mix 1 cup of brown sugar with ½ cup of ground cinnamon. Sprinkle on the pretzel and serve!'),
