(7035, 522, 'preparaciones_0_preparacion', 'Peel the pears and cut in half vertically. Use a spoon to remove the core. Then, add the pears to pan with schnapps, powdered sugar and lemon juice for 15 minutes over medium heat or until soft enough to be pierced with a fork.'),
(7036, 522, '_preparaciones_0_preparacion', 'field_58606bb7acb51'),
(7037, 522, 'preparaciones_1_preparacion', 'Using a slotted spoon, remove pears from the syrup and reserve. Continue to simmer the syrup left in the pan, simmering for a few minutes until it thickens.'),
(7038, 522, '_preparaciones_1_preparacion', 'field_58606bb7acb51'),
(7039, 522, 'preparaciones_2_preparacion', 'Melt the chocolate in water bath, with the butter, and ½ cup of sugar. When all the ingredients are well-blended, remove from heat and let cool.'),
(7040, 522, '_preparaciones_2_preparacion', 'field_58606bb7acb51'),
(7041, 522, 'preparaciones_3_preparacion', 'In a bowl beat 4 egg whites  with 3 tablespoon of sugar, until you get a meringue. Then pour the melt chocolate to the mixture, and mix it gently. Finally, put the isinglass sachet.'),
(7042, 522, '_preparaciones_3_preparacion', 'field_58606bb7acb51'),
(7043, 522, 'preparaciones_4_preparacion', 'Chill the mousse in the fridge for 30 minutes. Then, pour into a pastry sleeve.'),
(7044, 522, '_preparaciones_4_preparacion', 'field_58606bb7acb51'),
(7045, 522, 'preparaciones_5_preparacion', 'To serve, spread the bottom of the dish with the reserved syrup. Place a pear half cut side up and use pastry sleeve to fill each hole where the core used to be. If you do not have a pastry sleeve, you can carefully fill with a small spoon.'),
(7046, 522, '_preparaciones_5_preparacion', 'field_58606bb7acb51'),
