(7511, 556, 'preparaciones_0_preparacion', 'Pull the leaves off the spinach and wash them. Then fill a big bowl with water and bring to boil at medium heat. When the water is boiling, add a pinch of salt and the spinach. Now cook for about 1 or 2 minutes, turn the fire off and wash the leaves again but with cold water.'),
(7512, 556, '_preparaciones_0_preparacion', 'field_58606bb7acb51'),
(7513, 556, 'preparaciones_1_preparacion', 'Then, cut the spinach into fine stripes and mix it with the ricotta. Add salt, black pepper, and nutmeg to taste. Reserve it.'),
(7514, 556, '_preparaciones_1_preparacion', 'field_58606bb7acb51'),
(7515, 556, 'preparaciones_2_preparacion', 'Mix the flour with a pinch of salt, and the baking powder. Now melt the butter and pour it into the mixture, while adding a cup of warm water. Mix gently until you get a dough.'),
(7516, 556, '_preparaciones_2_preparacion', 'field_58606bb7acb51'),
(7517, 556, 'preparaciones_3_preparacion', 'Once you hace the dough, let it rest for 10 minutes inside a plastic bag.'),
(7518, 556, '_preparaciones_3_preparacion', 'field_58606bb7acb51'),
(7519, 556, 'preparaciones_4_preparacion', 'Turn dough out onto a floured work surface and stretch it with a rolling pin into a 0,2 inch thick round. Now cut 6 circles of 2 inches diameter each and brush the corners of every circle with some beaten egg.'),
(7520, 556, '_preparaciones_4_preparacion', 'field_58606bb7acb51'),
(7521, 556, 'preparaciones_5_preparacion', 'Now fill the center of every circle with the spinach mixture and close it making a half moon shape. Pay close attention to de corners: they have to be close enough. You can secure the corners by putting pressure with a fork. When they´re ready, brush them on top with beaten egg.'),
(7522, 556, '_preparaciones_5_preparacion', 'field_58606bb7acb51'),
(7523, 556, 'preparaciones_6_preparacion', 'Put the empanadas in a pre-heat oven at 392ºF for 8 minutes or until they´re brown.'),
