(7731, 568, 'preparaciones_0_preparacion', 'Wash the zucchinis, peel them and halve them. Take the seeds off with a spoons a cube them into ½ inch cubes. Season with sea salt to taste, and let them rest for 1 hour.'),
(7732, 568, '_preparaciones_0_preparacion', 'field_58606bb7acb51'),
(7733, 568, 'preparaciones_1_preparacion', 'In a pot bring water to boil and the vinegar. Now add the zucchinis and cook them for 4 minutes. Then strain the water and let them rest for a night (8 hours aprox). Now, dry them with paper.'),
(7734, 568, '_preparaciones_1_preparacion', 'field_58606bb7acb51'),
(7735, 568, 'preparaciones_2_preparacion', 'Now, you have to sterelize the 4 glass bottles (you have to place them in boiling water in a big pot). Dry them gently and put in each one: black pepper, the mustard seeds, the thyme, the garlic cloves, the zucchinis and the lemon slices. Now, cover all the ingredients with olive oil until reaches the top of the bottle.'),
(7736, 568, '_preparaciones_2_preparacion', 'field_58606bb7acb51'),
(7737, 568, 'preparaciones_3_preparacion', 'Now close the glass bottles and put them in water bath in a big pot with boiling water; the water must cover the entire bottle, except from the lid. Let them in water bath for 10 minutes. Then put them out of the heat and let them cold.'),
(7738, 568, '_preparaciones_3_preparacion', 'field_58606bb7acb51'),
(7739, 568, 'preparaciones_4_preparacion', 'Now you have to keep them in a dry-fresh place, without sun exposure. We recommend you to wait for at least a week before consuming, so the ingredients can blend together properly. The duration of the canned zucchinis are 8 weeks.'),
